verbose_text: The means of all serum Ca measures combined for all individuals heterozygous for each ClinVar and potential FHH1 or ADH1 missense variants are plotted in XREF_FIG C. Individuals with putative mGoF variants had significantly reduced mean serum Ca concentrations while all individuals having mLoF variants had mean serum Ca concentrations significantly higher than the REF (= ARE) haplotype and 9 of 12 variants had individuals who were overtly hypercalcemic (> = 10.2 mg/dL) (XREF_FIG C).
evidence: mGoF variants had significantly reduced mean serum Ca
